reviews.text:
I went to Eato during Restaurant Week lunch ($18 for 3 courses), and it was such a great experience. Parking was a little difficult with limited street parking, but I found out afterward that the Gateway Ramp nearby offers cheaper parking with a voucher ‚Äî good to know for next time!

The hostess was so thoughtful ‚Äî she noticed I had my iPad and seated me in a quiet area so I could work peacefully, which I really appreciated.

Food-wise, everything was on point. The red pepper bruschetta (just two pieces) was crunchy, chewy, and packed with flavor. The vodka pasta was rich and satisfying, and the cannoli was a light, sweet finish. Each portion was well-balanced ‚Äî I left feeling full but not heavy.

Great solo lunch spot with cozy vibes and excellent service. I‚Äôd definitely come back!

The non alcoholic drink selection is fantastic, and I love that there is a seasonal options menu. I try to avoid dairy and my server helped me figure out what could be made with a reduced amount of dairy. Super service and attention from her and the manager who brought us our food and came to check on us a few times.

Came in for restaurant week based on the $35 three course dinner menu. Reservation was required but it wasn't as busy at the time we came in, probably because it was a Monday.

For appetizers we started with the red pepper bruschetta and spinach dip (spinach, sundried tomato, fontina cheese, served with house-made deep fried pasta chips); entrees were both chicken Parmesan (mix of red and white sauce I believe, classic mozzarella, fresh garlic, and bucatini); then finishing with dessert of cannolis and tiramisu. All of it was excellent, I particularly liked the chicken Parmesan, the flavor of the sauce and bucatini paired with the presentation, chefs kiss. Very generous portion!

I would skip on the spinach dip, something about it just didn't hit as well as say a spinach artichoke dip but I'm definitely interested in coming back and trying other things on the menu! Great RW experience!

Excellent waitstaff, Mani was amazing, fun interior design and absolutly delicious pasta. We had the pesto pasta and they do not skimp on the pesto. Drenched complete and delicious in creamy pesto with pine nuts sprinkled over the dish.

Just ordered to go when I was in town.  Compliments to the chef that was working on the evening of 3/12/25!  Best fried ravioli I‚Äôve had to date.  Everything was cooked perfectly and the salmon was delish.  The veggie melody was very good also.  I recommend this spot.

editorial_summary.overview: Hip spot for internationally accented New American meals, plus sherry cocktails & wines.

detailedReviews.author: Jacob
detailedReviews.text: Excellent food.  We order the bruscetta, the field and forest pizza, and the beet salad and all three were in some degree new to us.  All great.  But the service is not just attentive; it goes beyond the call.  Just before arriving I had a too close encounter with a Minneapolis sidewalk; the staff could not have been helpful.  We ate early on a Wednesday in a half empty restaurant; when we left, it was nearly full.  I can see why.

detailedReviews.author: Sterling Vaughn
detailedReviews.text: Would definitely recommend! Impressed with the quality of service.

detailedReviews.author: Nick Blissenbach
detailedReviews.text: Summertime open air bar makes this a lovely spot for happy hour and dinner

detailedReviews.author: Travis S
detailedReviews.text: Great place,  the vodka sauce pasta and foccacia bread were delicious.  It is also a great deal to purchase a bottle of wine from the wine store with no corkage fee. Will be back!

detailedReviews.author: Jason Wolf
detailedReviews.text: Absolutely love everything about EaTo. Wonderful food, drinks & atmosphere. Our server Forrest was   the best!

detailedReviews.author: Diana Beutner
detailedReviews.text: We have been to Eato a few times because the food is quite good and there is a nice variety. That said the staff really needs some training. The atmosphere is on the loud side and the hostess spoke in a whisper and the waiter was also very quiet. I had to ask both of them to repeat things several times. We have sat near where the food comes out a couple of times and I just don't understand what the older men are doing.  Are they expediters? Managers? They seem to have perfected looking busy without doing much. They do not check on customers or interact with them at all. I made eye contact with one on my way out and he didn't ask how anything was or even nod or smile at me.

detailedReviews.author: Miranda Siedelmann
detailedReviews.text: The non alcoholic drink selection is fantastic, and I love that there is a seasonal options menu. I try to avoid dairy and my server helped me figure out what could be made with a reduced amount of dairy. Super service and attention from her and the manager who brought us our food and came to check on us a few times.

detailedReviews.author: Emily Jablonski
detailedReviews.text: Excellent waitstaff, Mani was amazing, fun interior design and absolutly delicious pasta. We had the pesto pasta and they do not skimp on the pesto. Drenched complete and delicious in creamy pesto with pine nuts sprinkled over the dish.

detailedReviews.author: Keith kozerski
detailedReviews.text: We love going to Eato!  The food is great!  Whether you want something casual and quick like pizza or something more substantial like chicken parm they do it really well.  The Eato staff are also friendly, attentive and professional.  Thanks for the consistently great experience.

detailedReviews.author: Kenn C
detailedReviews.text: Great service.   Excellent food.

detailedReviews.author: mehdi Hitane
detailedReviews.text: Manny was great tending to our table, proper service!

detailedReviews.author: Luci Borrell
detailedReviews.text: Food was amazing, service incredibly kind and helpful, and super cozy atmosphere!

detailedReviews.author: Libby Simones
detailedReviews.text: We return to EaTo time and time again because of the exceptional food, service and atmosphere!

detailedReviews.author: Laura
detailedReviews.text: I don‚Äôt know why this place doesn‚Äôt get more hype. I‚Äôve never had a bad meal (in fact, I think they have the best chicken/eggplant parm in the cities); the serving staff are always polite, helpful, and fun; and the atmosphere is great. Fun little market and good wine selection. Great happy hour deals and good bar menu! You get exactly what you pay for/it‚Äôs comparable to other restaurants in the area!

detailedReviews.author: Adam Wahlberg
detailedReviews.text: I picked up a grilled chicken sandwich for lunch and it was exquisite. My first time ordering from EaTo and I will be making it a habit.

detailedReviews.author: lizz Cristancho
detailedReviews.text: Very versatile menu, whether you order pizza or an entree, they are all good size and flavor. They have some fried gnocchi and wines in the happy-hour menu, 4-6 pm.

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Woodhouse
detailedReviews.text: Okay food small quantity‚Äôs for big price. We ordered fried mozzarella balls and got 12 small ones for 10$ as ‚Äúa happy hour deal‚Äù. Then charged extra for credit card. Service was also slow

detailedReviews.author: Jarrod Nelson
detailedReviews.text: EatOHNO! This was one of the worst meals I have ever had in Minneapolis. The food did not have a lick of seasoning. The salmon was so overcooked and the potatoes had zero flavor. The corpse reviver #2 was acceptable but ordered just a normal old fashioned which was awful. Sorry, but for $110 this should have been great. Very disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Hewan Dagmawi
detailedReviews.text:

detailedReviews.author: Amy McKee
detailedReviews.text: Lively atmosphere, attentive service, fantastic food! We were there for happy hour, and we loved the field and forest pizzette, the potato pave, and the meatballs. I also had an amazing banana negroni.

detailedReviews.author: mohammed mohammed
detailedReviews.text: Best panini‚Äôs ever! Super friendly and easy to order from. Highly recommend!

detailedReviews.author: Susie MacMillan
detailedReviews.text: We love eato. Their pizzas are our favorite. They are  amazing! We also love the staff. They have an excellent team and we are very grateful to have this spot in our neighborhood. Happy hour is also such a great deal!

detailedReviews.author: L
detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôve found the quality of the food at Eato to extremely inconsistent, usually falling on the unsatisfying side. Unfortunately there isn‚Äôt anything special about their menu. Sometimes you order a pizza and it‚Äôs thing and crispy, sometimes it‚Äôs thick and floppy. Sometimes the Caesar salad has great dressing, sometimes it tastes like mayo. We‚Äôve come here over 4 years and almost every time the food is drastically different in taste. I‚Äôm finally ready to stop trying to make the cute Italian wine shop a good place to eat.

detailedReviews.author: Lydz FHP
detailedReviews.text: The ac didn‚Äôt work, had to wave down our waitress for absolutely everything. This since the food wasn‚Äôt good. The shrimp scampi was tough and rubbery. Ordered a steak with the vodka penne and the steak looked like a dried up burger.

detailedReviews.author: Aldo Walker
detailedReviews.text: A very good Happy Hour on a Monday, when other restaurants choose to be closed.

detailedReviews.author: The Martin‚Äôs
detailedReviews.text: One of the worst piece of places in Minneapolis Minnesota. I ordered a pizza yesterday, July 4, 2025. I literally stay six minutes from this place I ordered a garden, veggie pizza and crispy potatoes only to receive a bag of garbage. My pizza was cold as ice in my potatoes are black and burnt. I actually saved it so I can upload a picture to show you guys proof I will never purchase from these guys again and I hope nobody else does as well.

detailedReviews.author: Juan David Garz√≥n Tob√≥n
detailedReviews.text: The food was very good. It's a small menu, with an Italian accent. Every ingredient was fresh and tasty, good service, very friendly. We will comeback.

detailedReviews.author: Christopher Smith
detailedReviews.text: Manny took care of our group of 20+. We ordered drinks, appetizers, dinner and desserts (sometimes multiple rounds). We kept Manny busy. He was gracious, kind, funny and completely on it the whole time. He even indulged us as we played a boisterous game of Mafia while he and his team worked diligently to serve our tables. One of the best large dinner experiences I've had and that's in large part due to Manny and the great team at EaTo.

detailedReviews.author: Luke Ailabouni
detailedReviews.text: Pasta is not freshly made and way overpriced, other dishes are great and happy hour food is excellent.

detailedReviews.author: Payge
detailedReviews.text: Drinks, pizza and dessert were all so good üíï

detailedReviews.author: Tim Gruenes
detailedReviews.text: Love eato!  Id highly recommend.  Awesome service and great food and happy hour specials.

detailedReviews.author: Brian Lewis
detailedReviews.text: Food was delicious and service was fantastic.

detailedReviews.author: Shannon Kelly
detailedReviews.text: Delicious food and drinks

detailedReviews.author: CWBW
detailedReviews.text: Love all the food we tried.  The pistachio cannoli was the best I have ever ate!  The meatballs were delicious.  Nice atmosphere and friendly staff.

detailedReviews.author: Laura Weiss
detailedReviews.text:
CANNOT GO WRONG HERE! It‚Äôs delicious. My husband and I have gone here several times, each time getting something new, and it‚Äôs been GREAT.

Favorites: The chicken parmesan pasta, the bolognese pasta, and the penne vodka pasta, their cocktails.

We haven‚Äôt tried the pizza yet, but we will be back!

detailedReviews.author: Zach Mills
detailedReviews.text: We stopped by EATO over the weekend and had a fantastic experience. The food was outstanding, our waitress was kind and attentive, and the management was clearly passionate about making every guest feel welcome. Beautiful and elegant space‚Äîperfect for dining in or grabbing something to go. Highly recommend!

detailedReviews.author: Saksham Puri
detailedReviews.text: The food was good and felt authentic; however, the menu had limited options overall. Good vibes, great interior.

detailedReviews.author: Deanna Ekholm
detailedReviews.text: I love, love, love Eato! We don't have a lot of options for downtown restaurants anymore, but that doesn't matter with Eato in town. The food is always consistent, the servers are amazing, I am never disappointed with my meal, it's always so fresh and exciting.

detailedReviews.author: Elle Maeyaert
detailedReviews.text: Stopped in for lunch because my social media has been flooded with Eato. My friend and I split an app and each had a salad and a non alcoholic cocktail. The fried brie was absolutely delicious. My beet salad was fine, the dressing overwhelmed the salad and made it very one note. The steak on his cesar was several levels overcooked (He ordered mid rare, it came out well) and bland. The beverages were yum, the entrees were lacking. I wish we had just split a couple more appetizers instead. Service was attentive and jovial. We enjoyed the banter. Eato is acceptable casual dining. It's a bit out of the way for me so I probably won't go back. There are just too many great options out there. If I've lived a short walk away, I'd probably give it another go.

detailedReviews.author: Melissa Jost
detailedReviews.text: Best service I‚Äôve had in a long time. I wish I could remember the server‚Äôs name. He was fabulous and would return just for him.

detailedReviews.author: Gabby
detailedReviews.text: I love this restaurant! I went today for lunch and Troy( who has been my server several times) was great! The service is great, they take dairy allergies seriously, and  it's always good food and wine!

detailedReviews.author: Josh Maxwell
detailedReviews.text: All amazing except Chicken Alfredo left something to be desired

detailedReviews.author: Lydia Anne
detailedReviews.text: love the vodka penne and have returned several times for it! very cute indoor atmosphere for a girls night, patio is also super nice for lunch or happy hour.

detailedReviews.author: S C
detailedReviews.text: Overpriced Overpriced Overpriced $31 for sub standard manicotti and focaccia bread. Very bland, lack of flavor. Stouffers is much better. Save your money

detailedReviews.author: Patricia Helmbrecht
detailedReviews.text: Long time customer.  Eato has excellent service and food!!  One of my favorite neighborhood restaurants!

detailedReviews.author: Melanie Wiesen
detailedReviews.text: Samuel Mitchell W. was the best, kindest server I have ever had. He absolutely stole our hearts. Give him a raise. Give him the keys to the city.

detailedReviews.author: Nicholas Gaspar
detailedReviews.text: One of the best restaurants in Minneapolis! We had the chicken parmesan, and it was delicious. The homemade pasta beautifully complemented the tender chicken, resulting in an unforgettable meal. All staff were extremely attentive to individual needs and allowed for some of the fastest service I have ever experienced.

detailedReviews.author: Jocelyne R
detailedReviews.text: Stopped by for dinner before heading to a concert at the U.S Bank Stadium and the service was great! Our waitress was really nice and thoughtful. The restaurant itself is super cute! I would recommend the Chicken Parmesan.

detailedReviews.author: Mary LaVoy
detailedReviews.text: EaTo is pricey, but I‚Äôve never left without enough for another meal at home. Pasta is fresh, happy hour menu makes it a great place for a quick bite before a show. Desserts are delicious, and the ice cream sandwich is highly recommended (as are the cannolis).

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Rolfes
detailedReviews.text: Good food, good service 5/5.

detailedReviews.author: Stephanie Adams
detailedReviews.text:
Great atmosphere, but got food poisoning from their chicken. My partner and I usually eat one meal as a late lunch/early dinner.

Then later that night following into next morning we became extremely nauseous & sick. The food was tasty and the service was good, but my experience afterwards was not enjoyable.

detailedReviews.author: mandy turpin
detailedReviews.text: The food was just okay.   Really wanted it to be better.   The fries were cold and the focaccia bread was dry.  Great location.

detailedReviews.author: Jake E
detailedReviews.text: Definitely the best Italian food beneath an apartment complex here in the Twin Cities!!! Our server Manny was phenomenal and should consider stand-up on the side; he was hilarious!!! Bolognese was very good, as the pasta tasted like it was made 13 minutes prior to dropping in the water. Definitely worth coming back for another date night! 9.19/10.00

detailedReviews.author: Tina Hagen
detailedReviews.text: The best shaved brussel sprout I‚Äôve ever had.  I‚Äôm already planning my next visit! The staff was exceptional and the environment was wonderful for a business lunch.

detailedReviews.author: Juanita
detailedReviews.text: Great place to eat I ordered Bolognese with house wine. I  tried their bubbly drink that tasted great. Great customer service and finally dessert was good.

detailedReviews.author: Lauren V
detailedReviews.text: I have not eaten at EaTo but I have had their food catered and it was delicious! Highly recommend. I look forward to dining in the next time!

detailedReviews.author: Lexi Leichtnam-Fitting
detailedReviews.text: I eloped in Minneapolis at the city hall and we had a large group reservation at Eato for lunch. The booking process to book the reservation space online was super easy. They were very responsive and it was exactly as I imagined! She helped give me the idea to have appetizers ready for my guests if they arrived before me and that worked out perfectly. The food also came pretty fast considering we were a group of 24! I highly recommend!!

detailedReviews.author: Ty'Aja Rodriguez
detailedReviews.text: The food was great. The drinks were fire. My server was cool! My only comment is they should have automatic gratuity on parties 6 or more.. My friend had her bday dinner here i was SO SHOCKED that there wasnt an auto gratuity üò≠ As a server i know how important that is. their policy is parties of 10 or more, but I think that‚Äôs kind of absurd

detailedReviews.author: Phil Zebleckis
detailedReviews.text: Just ordered to go when I was in town.  Compliments to the chef that was working on the evening of 3/12/25!  Best fried ravioli I‚Äôve had to date.  Everything was cooked perfectly and the salmon was delish.  The veggie melody was very good also.  I recommend this spot.

detailedReviews.author: Daniel Goldberg
detailedReviews.text: Very nice. Good food and nothing fancy.  Staff were very nice to us

detailedReviews.author: Lauryn Olson
detailedReviews.text: Extremely cute decor and small, cozy place, very friendly staff that tried to meet our needs and requests to the best of their ability, and delicious food!

detailedReviews.author: Tenzin
detailedReviews.text: the apps were really good, pastas were okay. service was good but really slow. would maybe come back for their happy hour but probably not

detailedReviews.author: Ann
detailedReviews.text: People here are rude. Not recommended.

detailedReviews.author: Jean Oshima
detailedReviews.text: Even if the pizza wasn‚Äôt as good as it was I‚Äôd probably come back here just for the service. I‚Äôve been witnessing a downturn in the level of customer service in this country. Doesn‚Äôt help that I‚Äôve just traveled to Japan where service of all kinds is impeccable. Today I stopped by EATO to order a pizza to go and you‚Äôd think I was at a Michelin-starred restaurant. The gentleman that welcomed me and took care of my order may have been the manager but acted like the owner! Excellent presence and demeanor, looked me in the eye as he spoke, offered me a glass of water while I waited for my order, let me know it would be about 15 minutes, and no more than 10 minutes later he delivered my piping hot pizza. And they were busy!! GREAT job EATO. I‚Äôll be back soon‚ù£Ô∏è

detailedReviews.author: Kiara Pederson
detailedReviews.text: All pastas were absolutely delicious!!!! Highly recommend fresh foccaccia with their ricotta spread. Yum!

detailedReviews.author: Lisa G. Korslund
detailedReviews.text: This is our local. Great staff, good food and wonderful vibe!

detailedReviews.author: Lauren Myhra
detailedReviews.text: Great vibes, delicious food, & a wide-variety of THC, alcoholic, and N/A drink options.

detailedReviews.author: rim woldeslassie
detailedReviews.text: The food and company were amazing, as always, but it was Manny's exceptional service that made our experience unforgettable. He‚Äôs honestly one of the best waiters I‚Äôve ever had‚Äîattentive, funny, and so kind. Manny made us feel like family, and I‚Äôd gladly return just to have him as our waiter again. He‚Äôs truly great at what he does, and with the combination of fantastic food and a welcoming atmosphere, I‚Äôll be back time and time again. Manny, thank you for being so wonderful. Hope to see you soon!üòä

detailedReviews.author: Collins s
detailedReviews.text: Great place to go! Love their lunch 1/2 sandwich 1/2 salad or soup. Love the roasted veggie sandwich.  We crave it!  Super friendly owner/mgrs.

detailedReviews.author: David Fettig
detailedReviews.text: Love Eato. Service impeccable. Ambience warm and inviting. Food? Perfetto!

detailedReviews.author: Jeremy Robinson
detailedReviews.text: Casual yet classy. Great date night destination. Two of their pizzas was plenty for the four of us. Umami and barbecue chicken. Both were fantastic and the price point was very comfortable. Great way staff took good care of us. We'll definitely add this to the rotation of downtown restaurants.
